args:
Unable to defeat Tsukuyomi, the party retreats.
But Izumo is not used to battle, and when he
lets his despair show, it angers Yukimura.
After their scuffle, Izumo's dual personality
Oki suddenly awakens, takes control of Shingen,
and defeats everyone but Yukimura.
Oh ho! You have some grit, little ones.\nBut your struggle remains laughable.
Aw, hell! Her wounds are healing!
Ah, but don't you know? It is impossible\nfor mere humans to defeat me.
There's no sense running our heads into\na wall here. Let's fall back and regroup.
Take the vanguard and guide them,\nFudo Myo-o. I will secure the rear.
Then I'll fight with you, General!

Multiple rear guards serve no purpose.
Also, no need to worry about meâ€”this
will just be a spot of exercise while the
rest of you get clear. Now go!
Okay, fineâ€”but you better come back!

So they fled, mmm? Well, I suppose I'll
simply deal with them in time. But as for
you, I trust you will at least make our
skirmish here entertaining?
I take no joy in fighting and wield my\nblade for the people. Now ready yourself!
*pant* *gasp* W-we made it out, but I\ndon't see the general anywhere!
You all can do as you please.\nI am going to Lord Shingen's side.
Wait, Fudo Myo-o! You're our guide!\nOh, bother. Where do we go now?
Guys, I see a river up ahead. It's almost\ndawn, so why don't we rest there awhile?
Good idea, Notte. We'll regroup and wait\nfor Shingen and Fudo Myo-o.
Still alive? After all that? My my.
Oh, but you ARE a sturdy one, aren't you?\nPerhaps you and I should play a new\nsort of game.
I've been curious for some time now what\nwould happen if a living human was\nflooded with Yomi chi.
Phew! I've finally caught my breath.\nTell me, darling, what do we do now?
Eventually we defeat Tsukuyomi. But as for\nright now, I'm afraid I'm a little short in\nthe ï¼‚brilliant planï¼‚ department.
That's because there are no plans left\nto be had.
Tsukuyomi is a dragon as powerful as\nLady Amaterasu herself.
And with her Yomi chi, she will rise again\nno matter how many times we defeat her.\nIt is a hopeless battle.
Sounds like you're scared of her.
Merely a statement of facts. We cannotâ€”

WRONG! That's not a fact, that's just your
OPINION! And in MY opinion, we can wipe
the floor with Tsukuyomi if we all just give
it everything we have!
And what could you possibly be basing\nsuch a thing on?
I just know it, all right? I know I can fight!
I can stand and I can hold a spear,\nwhich means I've still got fight in me\nno matter WHO the opponent is!
I'm not like you, Izumo! I'm not gonna\njust roll over and die like a coward!

Calm down, Yukimura. No need for that.
But that being said, Izumo, I don't think
things are quite so dire as you paint them
to be.
...I'm sorry. I need to be alone right now.
Leave him be, Yukimura. Let's all just take\na deep breath and figure out what our\nnext steps should be.
Actually, there's something we need to\nclear up first.
How did the Mukuroshu find us?\nHow was Fudo Myo-o's barrier broken?
Until we know that, we face the risk of\nanother ambush at any moment.
Yes, that is indeed strange. She said her\nbarrier could only be broken from the\ninside, did she not?
So you think we've got a mole? Or a rat?\nOr some other spy-like animal?!
I think we can rule that out; everyone with\nus has served the court or the shogunate\nsince their childhood.
Okay, so who broke the barrier? And how?
Lady Yukimura is mad! Oh, it's all well and\ngood to speak her bold words of never\ngiving up, but that's all they are! Words!
If we fight, we'll all die painful deaths at\nTsukuyomi's hands, and I...I don't want to\ngo through that.
Huh?! Who was that?! Where are you?!
I'm right here. Look at what you're holding.
The Eight-span Mirror? But all I see is...
That's right. You. The one who's listened\nto you all this time.
I don't understand this. Why is my\nreflection suddenly talking to me?
This hurts me, Izumo. No matter how many\ntimes we speak, you always forget about\nit afterward.
I know you don't want to fight, Izumo.\nSo lend me your body and let me do it\nfor you instead. Let me...
\n     t  a  k  e      y  o  u  r      p  l  a  c  e.
I am quite relieved to see you safe.\nNow let me escort you to the others.
Welcome back, Izumo. Shingen and Fudo\nMyo-o still haven't returned, so we are\ngoing to rest a bit longer beforeâ€”
He isn't coming back...because he was\nkilled by Lady Tsukuyomi's hand.
What are you talking about? And what do\nyou mean by ï¼‚Ladyï¼‚ Tsukuyomi?
I refer to my master, Lady Tsukuyomi.
Okay, I got no idea what's going on,\nbut this guy clearly ain't Izumo.
Ha ha! So you finally realized it, eh?\nYes, I'm Izumo's friend, Oki.
I'm also a member of the Mukuroshu...\nand Tsukuyomi's emissary.

So you're working for that awful dragon?
But why do you look like Izumo?! Does he
have some kind of evil twin no one
bothered to mention?
Look like him? No, no. This IS him.\nIt's just what's on the inside that's\ndifferent.
It's also how I was able to take down\nthat barrier before.

Of course! If this other side of Izumo's
personality surfaced while we were in the
barrier, it would have been a simple feat
to dismantle it.
Actually, most things are simple when \nyou're behind Izumo. You can get just\nabout anything you want.
Like this Underworld Key I needed to open\nthe Realm of the Dead.

The Eight-span Mirror...? Wait, do you
mean Amaterasu's dragon-treasure is
the same Underworld Key that revived
Tsukuyomi?!
I certainly did! You see, emissaries\nuse this thing to travel to Amaterasu's \naudience chamber.

That chamber is itself another world. So
that means the Eight-span Mirror has the
same power as an Underworld Key. 
It can open the Realm of the Dead.
The damn thing was sitting right in front\nof us this whole time and we missed it!

Ha ha! I bet you feel pretty stupid, huh?!
But now that Lady Tsukuyomi is revived,
your future plans of becoming the undead
are secured.
Aaanyway, I think that's enough talking.\nLady Tsukuyomi is waiting for all of you,\nso I'll just finish you off now. Good? Good!
You're welcome to try, kidâ€”but from\nwhere I stand, there's just one of you\nand a lot of us.
Oh, you silly thing! I'm not alone!
Wh-what are you doing, General?!\nYou have to stop this!

You're wasting your time The general has
been remade by Lady Tsukuyomi into a
soldier of the underworld, and he fears
not even death now.
No! You're lying! This is some kind of fake\nand FuMyo is off saving the real general!
Oh! Did you mean this thing?
FuMyo, no! What have you done,\nyou little creep?!
Me? I didn't do anything to her. He did.
You don't listen very well, do you?\nYour ï¼‚generalï¼‚ has already been remade.
General Shingen, no... Is that really you?
On me, Cleo! Let's fight 'em off! Haaah!
What the hell? It's like he doesn't even\ncare that he's getting attacked!
A soldier of the underworld who fears\nnot even death...
